  "content": "<table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"100%\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"min-width: 100%; \" class=\"stylingblock-content-wrapper\"><tr><td class=\"stylingblock-content-wrapper camarker-inner\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Verdana;\">Dear %%FirstName%%:<br>\n<br>\nDid you know that you can earn a concentration in Risk Management, Regulatory Compliance, Health Care Administration Law, Clinical Research Law or Cybersecurity Law when you earn your MS in Health Law? A concentration in one of these specialized areas along with your MS in Health Law will make you a more marketable professional. Learn more about our concentrations <a href=\"https://www.law.nova.edu/online/concentrations.html\">here</a>.<br>\n<br>\nI'm available to help you with the application process. The time to act is now so that we can get your application complete and get you started!<br>\n<br>\nPlease contact me at (954) 262-6367 or <a href=\"mailto:ed400@nova.edu\">ed400@nova.edu</a>&nbsp;right away so that I can help you complete your application for the online MS in Health Law.<br>\n  <br>\nYou can schedule a time to zoom or talk by clicking <a alias=\"here\" conversion=\"false\" data-linkto=\"https://\" href=\"https://calendly.com/nsulaw/lawprograms\" style=\"text-decoration:underline;\" title=\"here\">here</a>.<br>\n<br>\nSincerely,<br>\n<br>\nElizabeth DiBiase<br>\n954-262-6367 or 1-800-541-6682 ext.&nbsp; 26367<br>\n<a href=\"mailto:ed400@nova.edu\">ed400@nova.edu</a> </span></td></tr></table>",
